        "text": "Heh, it seems that my experience is exactly the opposite :sweat_smile: When I run projects they typically leave the platform configuration to the user. For example: \"this library requires packages , Y and optionally Z, please use your OS's package manager or provide the paths through environment variables\". Maybe it's a fault of the C\/C++ ecosystem. I've never seen CMake download and configure Windows SDK or VS Developer Tools.\n\nIn terms of cross-platformness it's rather limited. I only make sure it works of github's images for Windows, Ubuntu, on my Gentoo machine, and for anybody who reports a problem.",
